  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "In #55022 we observed a crashlooping controller cause a cluster cold boot failure, as controller-manager wasn't able to stay up long enough to run the deployment that would have fixed the problem.\r\n\r\nWe should audit everything that runs in kube-controller-manager and ensure that they all fail gracefully enough to prevent crashloops, or make them individually restart in that case, instead of the process.\r\n\r\nLonger term, we should consider classifying the controllers by run level or bootstrap order (#54522), and splitting them into separate binaries or changing the start-up order in kcm to make sure this sort of thing doesn't happen in the future.",
  "closed_at": "2019-01-24T19:54:22Z",
